cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CR 

This paper belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it investigates the behaviour of Twitter accounts in relation to political events. It also involves the analysis of large datasets, which could place it in the category of computers and society (cs.CY) or computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also touches on issues of cybersecurity and online manipulation, which could place it in the categories of social computing (cs.SOC) or cryptography and security (cs.CR).
